    "This evolution has led to the proliferation of IoT devices, with an estimated 10 billion active devices by the end of 2021 and a projected economic value of 4 up to 11 trillion by 2025 (Rangasamy et al. 2023).",
    "IoT has the potential to revolutionize various industries, including agriculture.",
    "It enables automated data collection, object communication, and human-machine interactions, leading to enhanced efficiency and convenience in areas such as transportation, healthcare, agriculture, energy, and manufacturing (Raja et al. 2023; Salama et al. 2023).",
    "By connecting devices like gadgets, cars, and appliances through sensors, software, and network connectivity, the IoT can fundamentally transform how we live and work, introducing a new era of interconnected and intelligent systems.",
    "In agriculture, the application of IoT is a groundbreaking technology that can be utilized year-round (Kim et al. 2020)."
